CNCP v1 40864
{
  "concept": "Flute",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-14T15:47:30.769095+00:00",
  "text": "The flute is a member of a family of musical instruments in the woodwind group. Like all woodwinds, flutes are aerophones, producing sound with a vibrating column of air. Flutes produce sound when the player's air flows across an opening. In the Hornbostel–Sachs classification system, flutes are edge-blown aerophones. A musician who plays the flute is called a flautist or flutist.\n",
  "language": "en",
